President Obama hosted the White House Science Fair to celebrate the winners of various science, technology, engineering, and math (STEM) competitions. The fair aimed to promote STEM education and inspire students to excel in these fields. The President also announced his appearance on an episode of Discovery Channel's MythBusters. Additionally, the Administration and leading companies announced initiatives to advance STEM education, such as placing 3D printers in schools and providing easy-to-use design tools for students. The fair showcased winning student projects, including a motorized chair for disabled students, a model solar car, research on interplanetary travel, safer sports helmets, and more.